<div id="main-article" class="article-content retro-folders">
<p></p><div class="quoteright" style="width:296px;"><div class="lazy_load_img_box" style="padding-top:35.14%"><img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/images/rsz_14c11ae4d8506c_2187.jpg" class="embeddedimage" border="0" alt="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/images/rsz_14c11ae4d8506c_2187.jpg" width="296" height="104"></div></div><div class="acaptionright" style="width:296px;">Whoever said "one is the loneliest number" never had to be player two.</div><p></p><div class="indent"><em>"Legends speak of a man who, from humble Italian beginnings, became one of the <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/VideoGame" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/VideoGame">video game</a> world's greatest most beloved heroes... He rescued damsels. He was a celebrity and a spokesman, a <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RenaissanceMan" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RenaissanceMan">renaissance man</a> who excelled in everything from sports to pharmaceutical studies. But despite his immense fame, this luminary was not above charitable causes like cleaning up the environment and helping children learn art, music, and even typing. And of course, he rescued more damsels. A prolific figure, his almost immeasurable list of accomplishments have inspired volumes upon volumes of comics. <br><br>This one is about that guy's little brother. He did stuff too, I think."</em><div class="indent">&mdash; <strong><a class="urllink" href="https://www.deviantart.com/kevinbolk/art/Lost-It-Sucks-To-Be-Weegie-Intro-790515313">This long lost intro comic<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a></strong></div></div><div class="proper-ad-unit mobile-ad square_ad"><h6 class="ad-caption">Advertisement:</h6><div id="proper-ad-tvtropes_mobile_ad_1"><script>propertag.cmd.push(function() { proper_display('tvtropes_mobile_ad_1'); })</script></div></div><p><em>It Sucks to Be Weegie</em> is a <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/SuperMarioBros" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/SuperMarioBros">Super Mario Bros.</a></em> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FanWebcomics" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FanWebcomics">fan webcomic</a> by Kevin "K-Bo" Bolk (whose other credits include <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Webcomic/ImMyOwnMascot" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Webcomic/ImMyOwnMascot">I'm My Own Mascot</a></em>, <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Webcomic/TriggerStar" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Webcomic/TriggerStar">Trigger Star</a></em>, and <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Webcomic/EnsignSueMustDie" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Webcomic/EnsignSueMustDie">Ensign Sue Must Die</a></em>), about, well... <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ExactlyWhatItSaysOnTheTin" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ExactlyWhatItSaysOnTheTin">how much it sucks to be Weegie</a>.</p><p>Luigi is your <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LoserProtagonist" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LoserProtagonist">run-of-the-mill loser</a> who is trying to get out of his brother's shadow (<a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheGhost" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheGhost">who incidentally never shows up in the comic</a>). The world is constantly out to get him, however. He starts out without a single friend, but as the series goes on he gains support from <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BigBeautifulWoman" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BigBeautifulWoman">Daisy</a>, <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheDitz" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheDitz">Rosalina</a> and <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheConfidant" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheConfidant">Link</a>.</p><p>Ended Christmas Day 2013. It can be found <a class="urllink" href="http://kevinbolk.deviantart.com/gallery/24576474">here<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a> on <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Website/DeviantArt" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Website/DeviantArt">DeviantArt</a>.</p><hr><div class="proper-ad-unit mobile-ad square_ad"><h6 class="ad-caption">Advertisement:</h6><div id="proper-ad-tvtropes_mobile_ad_2"><script>propertag.cmd.push(function() { proper_display('tvtropes_mobile_ad_2'); })</script></div></div><h2>This series contains examples of:</h2><ul><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AlternativeCharacterInterpretation" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AlternativeCharacterInterpretation">Alternative Character Interpretation</a>: <strong>Out the ears.</strong> Link is slight <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CampGay" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CampGay">Camp Gay</a>, Luigi has an inferiority complex, Daisy is <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AllWomenAreLustful" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AllWomenAreLustful">a pervert</a>, Peach is <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheDitz" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheDitz">The Ditz</a>, <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/SuperMarioGalaxy" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/SuperMarioGalaxy">Rosalina</a> is <em>even more</em> of a ditz, <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/Mother3" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/Mother3">Lucas</a> is a <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NietzscheWannabe" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NietzscheWannabe">Nietzsche Wannabe</a>, and <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/FZero" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/FZero">Captain Falcon</a> is <em>also</em> a ditz (and a <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Jerkass" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Jerkass">Jerkass</a>, for prank calling Luigi pretending to be <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/ShigeruMiyamoto" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/ShigeruMiyamoto">Shigeru Miyamoto</a> offering a pay rise).<span style="display:none">invoked</span></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AmbiguouslyBi" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AmbiguouslyBi">Ambiguously Bi</a>: Link. On one hand, he outright says he's gay and knows a few drag queens. On the other hand, after Luigi remarks on how he rejected <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/Metroid" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/Metroid">Samus's</a> offer for the time of his life, Link asks Luigi if he wants to go home with him and cry.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AnimatedActors" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AnimatedActors">Animated Actors</a>: The character's video game exploits occupy a weird space between this trope and actual adventures. It's most prominent with Link, though, <a class="urllink" href="http://kevinbolk.deviantart.com/art/Sucks-to-be-Weegie-Link-s-New-Job-275126607">who is explicitly referred to as being "on the set" of<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a> <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/TheLegendOfZeldaSkywardSword" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/TheLegendOfZeldaSkywardSword">Skyward Sword</a></em>.</li><div class="proper-ad-unit mobile-ad square_ad"><h6 class="ad-caption">Advertisement:</h6><div id="proper-ad-tvtropes_mobile_ad_3"><script>propertag.cmd.push(function() { proper_display('tvtropes_mobile_ad_3'); })</script></div></div><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ArsonMurderAndJaywalking" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ArsonMurderAndJaywalking">Arson, Murder, and Jaywalking</a>: Luigi's possible past lives were that of <a class="urllink" href="http://kevinbolk.deviantart.com/art/Sucks-to-be-Luigi-Past-Lives-163509497">dictators, murderers, and the Pringles Man<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AsideGlance" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AsideGlance">Aside Glance</a>: Luigi gives one in <a class="urllink" href="http://kevinbolk.deviantart.com/art/It-Sucks-to-be-Luigi-Freddie-158052850">this comic<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a>, as he realizes he can take advantage of the fact Rosalina mistakes him for Freddie Mercury.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BaitAndSwitch" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BaitAndSwitch">Bait-and-Switch</a>: In <a class="urllink" href="http://kevinbolk.deviantart.com/art/Sucks-to-be-Weegie-At-Last-252018568">one comic<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a>, the pudgy hero of the Mushroom Kingdom whose name starts with M is finally showing up in the comic! You're expecting it to be Mario, aren't you? <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> Nope, sorry, it's actually <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/SuperMarioRPG" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/SuperMarioRPG">Mallow</a>.</span></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BerserkButton" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BerserkButton">Berserk Button</a>: <a class="urllink" href="http://kevinbolk.deviantart.com/art/Sucks-to-be-Luigi-Wardrobe-180995021">Daisy's is claiming she's just a<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PaletteSwap" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PaletteSwap">Palette Swap</a> of Peach. <img src="/images/article-hreficon-ymmv.png" class="ymmv1 rounded" title="This example contains a YMMV entry. It should be moved to the YMMV tab."><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TranquilFury" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TranquilFury">Link's</a> <a class="urllink" href="http://kevinbolk.deviantart.com/art/Sucks-to-be-Weegie-Name-197584352">is pointing how he's hardly in the<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/IAmNotShazam" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/IAmNotShazam">titles for his games</a>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BetterAsFriends" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BetterAsFriends">Better as Friends</a>: <a class="urllink" href="http://kevinbolk.deviantart.com/art/It-Sucks-to-be-Luigi-Friends-156861516">Daisy tells Luigi this<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a>. He's just happy to <em>have</em> a friend.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BigBeautifulWoman" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BigBeautifulWoman">Big Beautiful Woman</a>: Daisy is made much chubbier than the other princesses. She's still quite cute. Cute enough to even have her own <a class="urllink" href="http://kevinbolk.deviantart.com/gallery/?q=daisy#/d2uwu3m">pin-up picture.<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a></li><li> <strong><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ButtMonkey" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ButtMonkey">Butt-Monkey</a></strong>: Luigi to a ridiculous degree. There's also the Goomba that complains about how he always has to worry about getting squashed... just for <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/StarFox" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/StarFox">Fox</a> <a class="urllink" href="http://kevinbolk.deviantart.com/art/Sucks-to-be-Luigi-Goombas-183397632">to trample him moments afterwards<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CelebrityResemblance" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CelebrityResemblance">Celebrity Resemblance</a>: An in-universe example happens when <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheDitz" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheDitz">Rosalina</a> <a class="urllink" href="http://kevinbolk.deviantart.com/art/It-Sucks-to-be-Luigi-Freddie-158052850">mistakes Luigi for<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Music/Queen" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Music/Queen">Freddie Mercury</a>. She keeps on calling him Freddie throughout the comic, and he doesn't mind.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheChewToy" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheChewToy">The Chew Toy</a>: Luigi.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CreepyChild" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CreepyChild">Creepy Child</a>: Lucas. It says something when <a class="urllink" href="http://kevinbolk.deviantart.com/art/S2BW-Falcon-s-Party-Part-3-262930222">quoting lyrics<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a> from <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Theatre/SweeneyToddTheDemonBarberOfFleetStreet" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Theatre/SweeneyToddTheDemonBarberOfFleetStreet">Sweeney Todd: The Demon Barber of Fleet Street</a></em> isn't out of character for him.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ADayInTheLimelight" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ADayInTheLimelight">A Day in the Limelight</a>/<a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AndNowForSomeoneCompletelyDifferent" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AndNowForSomeoneCompletelyDifferent">And Now for Someone Completely Different</a>: <a class="urllink" href="http://kevinbolk.deviantart.com/art/Sucks-To-Be-Weegie-It-s-Great-To-Be-Birdo-364366894">"It's Great to be Birdo!"<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheDitz" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheDitz">The Ditz</a>/<a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Cloudcuckoolander" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Cloudcuckoolander">Cloudcuckoolander</a>: Rosalina is a literal space case. She thinks Luigi is <em>Freddie Mercury</em>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheEeyore" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheEeyore">The Eeyore</a>: Lucas.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EldritchAbomination" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EldritchAbomination">Eldritch Abomination</a>: Rosalina paints a picture for Luigi. The painting is of "<img src="/images/article-hreficon-trivia.png" class="trivia1 rounded" title="This example contains a TRIVIA entry. It should be moved to the TRIVIA tab."><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FanNickname" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FanNickname">Weegee</a>", from the PC game <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/MarioIsMissing" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/MarioIsMissing">Mario Is Missing!</a>. Its eyes even move. <a class="urllink" href="http://kevinbolk.deviantart.com/art/Sucks-to-be-Luigi-Portrait-167895951">Naturally, Luigi freaks out.<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EnfantTerrible" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EnfantTerrible">Enfant Terrible</a>: <a class="urllink" href="http://kevinbolk.deviantart.com/art/Sucks-to-be-Luigi-Mario-Kart-153670444">Baby Peach.<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EvilCounterpart" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EvilCounterpart">Evil Counterpart</a>: Luigi has one in the form of Waluigi, who constantly mocks him despite the fact he may be the one person who actually sucks more than Luigi. Luigi even calls him out on it. See <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheReasonYouSuckSpeech" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheReasonYouSuckSpeech">"The Reason You Suck" Speech</a>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ExactWords" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ExactWords">Exact Words</a>: <a class="urllink" href="http://kevinbolk.deviantart.com/art/Sucks-2B-Weegie-Daisy-s-Book-198874497">Well played princess...<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GamerGirl" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GamerGirl">Gamer Girl</a>: Daisy.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheGhost" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheGhost">The Ghost</a>: Mario. Despite being mentioned a lot for his heroics, Luigi's more popular brother never appears in the comic. Wonderfully lampshaded in <a class="urllink" href="http://tiny.cc/nc7zax">this<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a> background, and in the eyesight test in the comic Playing Doctor.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Gonk" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Gonk">Gonk</a>: <a class="urllink" href="http://kevinbolk.deviantart.com/art/Sucks-to-be-Luigi-Advice-158550188">Wario<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a>, <a class="urllink" href="http://kevinbolk.deviantart.com/art/Sucks-to-be-Luigi-Nemesis-p-1-172169334">Waluigi<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a>, and <a class="urllink" href="http://kevinbolk.deviantart.com/art/Sucks-to-be-Luigi-Her-Type-165983436">Donkey Kong<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GoshDangItToHeck" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GoshDangItToHeck">Gosh Dang It to Heck!</a>: Luigi swears this way.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HaveIMentionedIAmGay" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HaveIMentionedIAmGay">Have I Mentioned I Am Gay?</a>: Link.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HeroicMime" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HeroicMime">Heroic Mime</a>: Averted with Link. He <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Handwave" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Handwave">handwaves</a> it by saying he just doesn't get to talk a lot in his day job.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HeterosexualLifePartners" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HeterosexualLifePartners">Heterosexual Life-Partners</a>/<a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/OddFriendship" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/OddFriendship">Odd Friendship</a>: Luigi and Link... even though Link isn't actually heterosexual.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/IncompatibleOrientation" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/IncompatibleOrientation">Incompatible Orientation</a>: Daisy <em>immediately</em> falls head-over-heels in love with Link... too bad for her that Link is <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/StraightGay" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/StraightGay">Straight Gay</a>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/InterspeciesRomance" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/InterspeciesRomance">Interspecies Romance</a>: Between <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/DonkeyKong" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/DonkeyKong">Pauline and Donkey Kong</a>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Jerkass" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Jerkass">Jerkass</a>:<ul><li> Waluigi and Captain Falcon. Zelda is one.</li><li> Captain Falcon may actually be acting like a <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Jerkass" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Jerkass">Jerkass</a> to cover up the fact that he's actually just as lonely as Luigi.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LocalHangout" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LocalHangout">Local Hangout</a>: "Sub-Space," which is a bar where Luigi, Link, and Daisy often hang out.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NiceCharacterMeanActor" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NiceCharacterMeanActor">Nice Character, Mean Actor</a>: Zelda, apparently.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NiceGuy" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NiceGuy">Nice Guy</a>: Link</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NoodleIncident" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NoodleIncident">Noodle Incident</a>: Link mentions an "incident in '93" at one point. Zelda does the same later. Then again, <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/TheLegendOfZeldaCDiGames" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/TheLegendOfZeldaCDiGames">given what we know about certain Zelda games released in 1993</a>, it's probably for the best that they don't elaborate.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PuppyDogEyes" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PuppyDogEyes">"Sad Octorock" Face</a>: Luigi's are strong enough to <em> <a class="urllink" href="http://kevinbolk.deviantart.com/art/S2BW-Falcon-s-Party-Part-1-259494302">work through the phoneline<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a></em>. Mario also <a class="urllink" href="http://kevinbolk.deviantart.com/art/Sucks-to-Be-Luigi-Costumes-164370755">apparently<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a> has them.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheReasonYouSuckSpeech" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheReasonYouSuckSpeech">"The Reason You Suck" Speech</a>: <a class="urllink" href="http://kevinbolk.deviantart.com/art/Sucks-to-be-Luigi-Nemesis-p-3-174853915">Luigi gives quite a nasty one to Waluigi<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a> after he's spent two comics <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Troll" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Troll">trolling</a> Luigi. In fact, he begins to tear up afterwards. When Luigi starts to feel bad for it, <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/JerkWithAHeartOfJerk" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/JerkWithAHeartOfJerk">Waluigi</a> takes advantage of the opportunity and gives him an atomic wedgie.<div class="indent"> <strong>Luigi:</strong> I suck? <em>I</em> suck!?! Look who's talking, you freak! How many games have you been in, huh? <em>Mario Tennis?</em> Yeah, real winner there. And what? Did you wake up one morning and think "I'm sick of playing with myself. I should do something with my life. I know! I'll dress up like a crappy evil clone of a second-string video game character." Yeah, way to aim high, pal. I may have low self-esteem but I think you are the only person who actually sucks more than I do. So you can take your "secret message" and <strong>SHOVE IT WHERE THE WARP PIPES DON'T GO!!</strong></div></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SamusIsAGirl" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SamusIsAGirl">Samus Is a Girl</a>: ...except Luigi doesn't know that. <a class="urllink" href="http://kevinbolk.deviantart.com/art/Sucks-to-be-Luigi-Flirting-179624896">When she offered him the time of his life, Luigi refused, saying that he didn't swing that way.<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SorryImGay" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SorryImGay">Sorry, I'm Gay</a>: Link. <img src="/images/article-hreficon-trivia.png" class="trivia1 rounded" title="This example contains a TRIVIA entry. It should be moved to the TRIVIA tab."><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ImageSource" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ImageSource">Provides the trope image</a>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/StealthInsult" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/StealthInsult">Stealth Insult</a>: "I assure you, no one could possibly think less of you than they already do."</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/StrawNihilist" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/StrawNihilist">Straw Nihilist</a>: <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/MOTHER3" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/MOTHER3">Lucas</a>, as seen <a class="urllink" href="http://kevinbolk.deviantart.com/art/Sucks-to-be-Weegie-Lucas-202977317">here.<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TakeThat" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TakeThat">Take That!</a>:<ul><li> <a class="urllink" href="http://kevinbolk.deviantart.com/art/Sucks-to-be-Luigi-Blind-Date-154319483">Peach describes<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/Twilight" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/Twilight">Twilight</a> as "those trashy vampire novels".</li><li> The comic takes <a class="urllink" href="http://kevinbolk.deviantart.com/art/Sucks-to-be-Luigi-Propeller-155015740">a few<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a> <a class="urllink" href="http://kevinbolk.deviantart.com/art/Sucks-to-Be-Luigi-Costumes-164370755">digs at the outfits in<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/SuperMarioGalaxy" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/SuperMarioGalaxy">Super Mario Galaxy</a> and <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/NewSuperMarioBros" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/NewSuperMarioBros">New Super Mario Bros.</a></li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheTeaser" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheTeaser">The Teaser</a>: Every comic starts with a remark from Luigi. Sometimes they are related to the comic, but more often they're just further looks at how much it sucks to be him.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheUnfavourite" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheUnfavourite">The Un-Favourite</a>: It wasn't really surprising when <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ButtMonkey" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ButtMonkey">Luigi</a> was revealed to be one. In an earlier comic, he says that he was apparently Mama's favourite "Not-Mario". Poor Luigi. Taken to an incredibly pitiful level <a class="urllink" href="http://kevinbolk.deviantart.com/art/Sucks-to-be-Weegie-Baby-274139325">here.<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ThisLoserIsYou" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ThisLoserIsYou">This Loser Is You</a>: Luigi.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ThrowTheDogABone" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ThrowTheDogABone">Throw the Dog a Bone</a>:<ul><li> In the finale, he <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">gets a compliment and a kiss from Toadette.</span></li><li> There are a few other instances, such as when he set up a free hugs booth but didn't get any hugs <a class="urllink" href="http://kevinbolk.deviantart.com/art/Sucks-2b-Weegie-Hugs-Part-3-243604727">so Link takes him out for ice-cream<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a>.</li><li> And the "Launch party".</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WhenLifeGivesYouLemons" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WhenLifeGivesYouLemons">When Life Gives You Lemons...</a>: <a class="urllink" href="http://kevinbolk.deviantart.com/art/Sucks-to-Be-Luigi-Costumes-164370755">...be thankful it didn't give you rocks.<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WoundedGazelleGambit" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WoundedGazelleGambit">Wounded Gazelle Gambit</a>: Waluigi pretends to be hurt by Luigi's beatdown of him in order to lure him in for an atomic wedgie.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WrongGenreSavvy" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WrongGenreSavvy">Wrong Genre Savvy</a>: <a class="urllink" href="http://kevinbolk.deviantart.com/art/Sucks-2B-Weegie-Party-Prelude-258392621">Captain Falcon impersonates Shigeru Miyamoto and pulls a prank on Luigi by saying that it is the Year of Luigi.<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a> <a class="urllink" href="http://kevinbolk.deviantart.com/art/It-Sucks-To-Be-Weegie-2013-362874085">When Satoru Iwata calls about the same thing, Luigi thinks it is another prank, and rages at him.<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/YaoiFangirl" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/YaoiFangirl">Yaoi Fangirl</a>: Daisy is one, if her <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/KingdomHearts" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/KingdomHearts">Axel/Roxas</a> poster is anything to go by. Also perhaps why she's not deterred by Link outright telling her he's gay...</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/YourPrincessIsInAnotherCastle" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/YourPrincessIsInAnotherCastle">Your Princess Is in Another Castle!</a>: Referenced in the first comic.</li></ul><hr>
</div>
